oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The Stars and Stripes February 14, 1919
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The Stars and Stripes publication from Feb. 14, 1919 describing and commemorating the Ambulance Corps.

Stars and Stripes was a newspaper published by the American Expeditionary Forces (AEF) in occupied France. General John J. Pershing requested that it be created to boost morale. It was written for and by servicemen, and it ran from February 8, 1918 to June 13, 1919.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Robert Frank Hodge World War I Papers, 1914-1919
